File::NCopy

copy()          Copies file to file or files/directories to a directory.

cp()            Just an alias for copy.

The below are only for the object oriented features.

new()           When used as an object, it's used for instatiation.

preserve()      Preserve some of the originating file's attributes.

recursive()     Set the recursive flag. 

follow_links()  Follow symbolic links instead of just recreating them.

To install :

perl Makefile.PL
make
make install

